would it hurt my cat to brush her teeth with human toothpaste if so how can i freshen her breath without people tooth paste is not good for dogs or cats it can make them sick i understand you don't want to spend a lot of money so why don't you try going to the vet to see what they have to offer in their store i use cet chews my cats love them apparently they taste good and you can give them to the cat once a day or ever few days there are also a variety of rinses you can use and there is also the stuff that you put in her water pet tooth paste doesn't cost that much keep in mind that you don't have to brush the inside of your cat's teeth like we do just brusth the out side and you don't have to brush them for as long as minutes a quick wipe is good you might want to get your cat's teeth looked at by a vet to determine if she has bad teeth if she has bad teeth no amount of brushing or rinsing is going to get rid of the bad breath she will need a dental to help get rid of bad breath check with the vet to see if they offer discounts february is usually dental month for vets and they usually have discounts at that time all of the above is information i learned while working for a vet in the last years remember if your cat has bad teeth the only way to fix the bad breath is by doing a dental the other stuff is mainly preventative good luck Halitosis Tooth enamel Tooth Fluoride therapy Dental caries Guinea pig The Fairly OddParents Cat Domestic rabbit Fancy rat Toothpaste Pet skunk Garfield Kim Possible Time Out of Mind First aid Dog training Ferret Glossitis 2000 Australian Grand Prix Pitaten Hamster Neopets Gingivitis Randomness Chewing gum Mutual fund Rocko's Modern Life Dentistry Dental brace Non-native pronunciations of English RuneScape quests Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Socialization Richard Chase The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Sinfest Muslim ibn Aqeel Phoebe Buffay's songs Rich Mullins Codename: Kids Next Door 